## Location
services/mysql-change-stream/cmd/server/main.go:124-144

## Issue
The goroutine processing changes never terminates on error. It keeps running when a new client is created, leading to memory accumulation and resource exhaustion.

```go
go func(c *server.Client) {
    for {
        select {
        case <-ctx.Done():
            return
        case change, ok := <-c.Changes():
            if !ok {
                return
            }
            if err := buffer.AddChange(ctx, change); err != nil {
                log.Printf("Error storing change in KV: %v", err)
            }
            // ...
        }
    }
}(client)
```

If `buffer.AddChange()` returns an error, the goroutine continues. When a new client is created, the old goroutine may still be running.

## Fix
Track goroutines and ensure proper cleanup when client is replaced or closed.
